# In-Memory Python Console Todo App (Phase I)

A command-line todo application in Python that operates entirely in memory with no external storage. The application provides core todo management features through a CLI interface.

## Features

- Add new todos
- View all todos
- Update existing todos
- Delete todos
- Mark todos as complete/incomplete

## Installation

```bash
pip install .
```

Or run directly:

```bash
python -m src.todo_app.cli.main
```

## Usage

Start the application:

```bash
todo-app
```

Available commands:

- `add "todo description"` - Add a new todo
- `view` - View all todos
- `update <id> "new description"` - Update a todo
- `delete <id>` - Delete a todo
- `complete <id>` - Mark a todo as complete
- `incomplete <id>` - Mark a todo as incomplete
- `quit` or `exit` - Exit the application

## Example

```
> add "Buy groceries"
Todo added with ID: 1

> add "Walk the dog"
Todo added with ID: 2

> view
ID  | Title           | Status
----|-----------------|--------
1   | Buy groceries   | Pending
2   | Walk the dog    | Pending

> complete 1
Todo 1 marked as complete

> view
ID  | Title           | Status
----|-----------------|--------
1   | Buy groceries   | Complete
2   | Walk the dog    | Pending

> quit
```

## Architecture

The application follows a clean architecture pattern with:

- **Models**: Todo entity and TodoList collection
- **Repositories**: In-memory storage implementation
- **Services**: Business logic layer
- **CLI**: Command-line interface layer

## Testing

Run the tests with:

```bash
pytest
```

Tests are organized in:
- `tests/unit/` - Unit tests for individual components
- `tests/integration/` - Integration tests for command flows
